folder: Pike Street & Madison Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
(1) Pike Street, west side, north from but not including Madison, to, but not including Henry Streets. The view shows a Synagogue, The Congregation Aushel Slusk, at No, 34 Pike Street.
NEG: 2908  July 25, 1931.

P. L. Sperr.

(2) The same, showing a closer view of 36 to 32 Pike Street, west side, between Madison and Henry Streets. 34 Pike Street is the Synagogue of the Congregation Anshei Slusk.
October 28, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.

(3) The same, as No. 1, showing a closer view of Nos. 26-28 Pike Street, at and adjoining the S.W. corner of Henry Street.
NEG. 2909  July 25, 1931.

P. L. Sperr.
